<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3464] Error in the Console when running a GroovyTestCase 2 times.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3464</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I do not know if we should run twice a test in GroovyConsole, but when we do it the interrupt msgbox stays there and it is not possible to close it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To reproduce the error. Open the console in Ubuntu 8.10 (I have no idea if this happens in other environments) &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Execute the following test case:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; groovy.util.GroovyTestCase

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;AnyTest &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; GroovyTestCase {

    void testAssertAnyStuff() {
        assertEquals &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;1&apos;&lt;/span&gt;
    }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It runs ok.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then run again, the window to interrupt the script does not close, even if we press &quot;Interrupt&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Ubuntu 8.10</environment>
