                            <comment id="14466796" author="eniosp" created="Tue, 14 Apr 2009 05:55:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, this is very wired.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just tested again and it happened after the 4th try. Unfortunately I have only Ubuntu here, so I do not know if it can be reproduced on Mac or windows.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466907" author="blackdrag" created="Tue, 14 Apr 2009 11:15:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;unfortunately it looks like Ubuntu&apos;s Gnome desktop and Swing work well together. I am not sure that is the reason for the bug here, but it is an additional error source. I noticed these kind of problems when working for example with Intellij IDEA on Ubuntu. Sometimes it is nearly unusable, because dialog boxes tend to be empty.  I suggest you install twm and then start a xsession with twm instead with gnome. Should the error happen there too, then it is most probably not realted to the gnome window manager.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466764" author="eniosp" created="Tue, 14 Apr 2009 13:09:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi it looks like this is a buggy behavior in Ubuntu. not necessarily related to unit tests. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A script like the one bellow:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;3.times { println it }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; 

&lt;p&gt;If you run it multiple times the error happens.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this incident can be closed, maybe more related to Ubuntu than to Groovy console.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
